ONE person has died following a fire at a top floor flat in Livingston today.
Scottish Fire and Rescue appliances were called to Tweed Drive in the town’s Craigshills area shortly before 3pm.
It is believed a body was found by firefighters who forced entry to the property which was well alight when emergency services arrived.
Police closed off local streets as neighbours watched from the road outside the scene of the fire.
Police Scotland said they could not confirm that the victim was a woman.
A spokesman for Police Scotland said: “Emergency services in West Lothian were called to a house fire on Tweed Drive, Livingston, at around 3pm today.
“A body has been found on the premises and an enquiry into the full circumstances is currently ongoing.”
Fire Services are are still on the scene.
